import jinja2

thought_1 = "If I were dramatically smarter, I could write software like that."
thought_2 = "Machines never have this problem, only humans."
thought_3 = "I wish I knew more about code sprites and privacy concerns."

jinja = jinja2.Environment()
jinja.autoescape = False

template = jinja.from_string("""
thought_1 = {{ thought_1 }}
thought_2 = {{ thought_2 }}
thought_3 = {{ thought_3 }}
""")

template.render(
    thought_1=thought_1,
    thought_2=thought_2,
    thought_3=thought_3
)
